Class.Name: NSAttributedString
Class.Description: A string with associated attributes (such as visual style, hyperlinks, or accessibility data) for portions of its text.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithString:
InstanceMethods.Description: Creates an attributed string with the characters of the specified string and no attribute information.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithString:attributes:
InstanceMethods.Description: Creates an attributed string with the specified string and attributes.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithAttributedString:
InstanceMethods.Description: Creates an attributed string with the characters and attributes of the specified attributed string.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithData:options:documentAttributes:error:
InstanceMethods.Description: Creates an attributed string from the data in the specified data object.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithDocFormat:documentAttributes:
InstanceMethods.Description: Creates an attributed string from Microsoft Word format data in the specified data object.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithHTML:documentAttributes:
InstanceMethods.Description: Creates an attributed string from the HTML in the specified data object.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithHTML:baseURL:documentAttributes:
InstanceMethods.Description: Creates an attributed string from the HTML in the specified data object and base URL.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithHTML:options:documentAttributes:
InstanceMethods.Description: Creates an attributed string from the HTML in the specified data object.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithRTF:documentAttributes:
InstanceMethods.Description: Creates an attributed string by decoding the stream of RTF commands and data in the specified data object.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithRTFD:documentAttributes:
InstanceMethods.Description: Creates an attributed string by decoding the stream of RTFD commands and data in the specified data object.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithRTFDFileWrapper:documentAttributes:
InstanceMethods.Description: Creates an attributed string from the specified file wrapper that contains an RTFD document.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithURL:options:documentAttributes:error:
InstanceMethods.Description: Creates an attributed string from the contents of the specified URL.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithMarkdownString:options:baseURL:error:
InstanceMethods.Description: Creates an attributed string from a Markdown-formatted string using the provided options.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithMarkdown:options:baseURL:error:
InstanceMethods.Description: Creates an attributed string from Markdown-formatted data using the provided options.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithContentsOfMarkdownFileAtURL:options:baseURL:error:
InstanceMethods.Description: Creates an attributed string from the contents of a specified URL that contains Markdown-formatted data using the provided options.

InstanceMethods.Name: attributesAtIndex:effectiveRange:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the attributes for the character at the specified index.

InstanceMethods.Name: attributesAtIndex:longestEffectiveRange:inRange:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the attributes for the character at the specified index and, by reference, the range where the attributes apply.

InstanceMethods.Name: attribute:atIndex:effectiveRange:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the value for an attribute with the specified name of the character at the specified index and, by reference, the range where the attribute applies.

InstanceMethods.Name: attribute:atIndex:longestEffectiveRange:inRange:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the value for the attribute with the specified name of the character at the specified index and, by reference, the range where the attribute applies.

InstanceMethods.Name: isEqualToAttributedString:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a Boolean value that indicates whether the attributed string is equal to another attributed string.

InstanceMethods.Name: attributedSubstringFromRange:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an attributed string consisting of the characters and attributes within the specified range in the attributed string.

InstanceMethods.Name: enumerateAttribute:inRange:options:usingBlock:
InstanceMethods.Description: Executes the specified block for each range of a particular attribute in the attributed string.
InstanceMethods.Declaration:
- (void)enumerateAttribute:(NSAttributedStringKey)attrName 
                   inRange:(NSRange)enumerationRange 
                   options:(NSAttributedStringEnumerationOptions)opts 
                usingBlock:(void (^)(id value, NSRange range, BOOL *stop))block;

InstanceMethods.Name: enumerateAttributesInRange:options:usingBlock:
InstanceMethods.Description: Executes the specified block for each range of attributes in the attributed string.

InstanceMethods.Name: fontAttributesInRange:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the font attributes in effect for the character at the specified location.

InstanceMethods.Name: rulerAttributesInRange:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the ruler (paragraph) attributes in effect for the characters within the specified range.

InstanceMethods.Name: doubleClickAtIndex:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the range of characters that form a word (or other linguistic unit) surrounding the specified index, taking language characteristics into account.

InstanceMethods.Name: lineBreakBeforeIndex:withinRange:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the appropriate line break when the character at the index doesn’t fit on the same line as the character at the beginning of the range.

InstanceMethods.Name: lineBreakByHyphenatingBeforeIndex:withinRange:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the index of the closest character before the specified index, and within the specified range, that can fit on a new line by hyphenating.

InstanceMethods.Name: nextWordFromIndex:forward:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the index of the first character of the word after or before the specified index.

InstanceMethods.Name: itemNumberInTextList:atIndex:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the index of the item at the specified location within the list.

InstanceMethods.Name: rangeOfTextBlock:atIndex:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the range of the individual text block that contains the specified location.

InstanceMethods.Name: rangeOfTextList:atIndex:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the range of the specified text list that contains the specified location.

InstanceMethods.Name: rangeOfTextTable:atIndex:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the range of the specified text table that contains the specified location.

InstanceMethods.Name: dataFromRange:documentAttributes:error:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a data object that contains a text stream corresponding to the characters and attributes within the specified range.

InstanceMethods.Name: fileWrapperFromRange:documentAttributes:error:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a file wrapper object that contains a text stream corresponding to the characters and attributes within the specified range.

InstanceMethods.Name: docFormatFromRange:documentAttributes:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a data object that contains a Microsoft Word–format stream corresponding to the characters and attributes within the specified range.

InstanceMethods.Name: RTFFromRange:documentAttributes:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a data object that contains an RTF stream corresponding to the characters and attributes within the specified range, omitting all attachment attributes.

InstanceMethods.Name: RTFDFromRange:documentAttributes:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a data object that contains an RTFD stream corresponding to the characters and attributes within the specified range.

InstanceMethods.Name: RTFDFileWrapperFromRange:documentAttributes:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a file wrapper object that contains an RTFD document corresponding to the characters and attributes within the specified range.

InstanceMethods.Name: drawAtPoint:
InstanceMethods.Description: Draws the attributed string starting at the specified point in the current graphics context.

InstanceMethods.Name: drawInRect:
InstanceMethods.Description: Draws the attributed string inside the specified bounding rectangle in the current graphics context.

InstanceMethods.Name: drawWithRect:options:context:
InstanceMethods.Description: Draws the attributed string in the specified bounding rectangle using the provided options.

InstanceMethods.Name: size
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the size necessary to draw the string.

InstanceMethods.Name: boundingRectWithSize:options:context:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the bounding rectangle necessary to draw the string.

InstanceMethods.Name: containsAttachmentsInRange:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a Boolean value that indicates if the attributed string contains an attachment in the specified range.

InstanceProperties.Name: string
InstanceProperties.Description: The character contents of the attributed string as a string.

InstanceProperties.Name: length
InstanceProperties.Description: The length of the attributed string.

TypeMethods.Name: attributedStringWithAttachment:
TypeMethods.Description: Creates an attributed string with an attachment.

TypeMethods.Name: loadFromHTMLWithRequest:options:completionHandler:
TypeMethods.Description: Creates an attributed string by converting the contents of the specified HTML URL request.

TypeMethods.Name: loadFromHTMLWithFileURL:options:completionHandler:
TypeMethods.Description: Creates an attributed string by converting the contents of a local HTML file at the specified URL.

TypeMethods.Name: loadFromHTMLWithString:options:completionHandler:
TypeMethods.Description: Creates an attributed string from the specified HTML string.

TypeMethods.Name: loadFromHTMLWithData:options:completionHandler:
TypeMethods.Description: Creates an attributed string from the specified HTML data.

TypeProperties.Name: textTypes
TypeProperties.Description: An array of UTI strings that identify the file types that attributed strings support, either directly or through a user-installed filter service.

TypeProperties.Name: textUnfilteredTypes
TypeProperties.Description: An array of UTI strings that identify the file types that attributed strings support directly.
